ZH: 我的朋友失败后不要灰心，要继续努力。
EN: My friend should not be disheartened after failure, but continue to work hard.

ZH: 虽然你经历了失败，也别灰心。
EN: Even though you have encountered failure, do not be discouraged.

ZH: 对于困难的挑战，不要轻易灰心。
EN: Do not easily lose heart when faced with tough challenges.

ZH: 尽管我们遇到困难，但我们不能灰心。
EN: Although we encounter difficulties, we cannot lose heart.

ZH: 灰心会让你的自信心受到伤害。
EN: Being disheartened will hurt your confidence.

ZH: 我的目标是永远不灰心，坚持到底。
EN: My goal is to never lose heart and persevere till the end.

ZH: 当事情没有如我们所愿时，我们很容易灰心。
EN: We are easily disheartened when things don't go our way.

ZH: 他经历了很多挫折，但从不灰心。
EN: He has faced many setbacks, but never gets disheartened.

ZH: 拥有信心可以帮助你战胜灰心。
EN: Having confidence can help you overcome disheartenment.

ZH: 灰心的人往往容易放弃。
EN: Disheartened individuals tend to give up easily.

ZH: 不管遭遇多少次失败，你都不能灰心丧气。
EN: No matter how many failures you encounter, you must not lose heart.

ZH: 面对困难时，我们不能灰心丧气。
EN: We must not lose heart when faced with difficulties.

ZH: 即使面对挑战，也不能灰心放弃。
EN: Even when facing challenges, we must not lose heart and give up.

ZH: 灰心只会让困境变得更加艰难。
EN: Being disheartened will only make the situation more difficult.

ZH: 他在奋斗中从不灰心，在逆境中更加坚强。
EN: He never loses heart in his struggle, and becomes stronger in adversity.

ZH: 遇到困难时，我们应该相互鼓励，不要灰心。
EN: When faced with difficulties, we should encourage each other and not lose heart.

ZH: 不管多么失望，我们都不能灰心。
EN: No matter how disappointed we are, we must not lose heart.

ZH: 他不惧困难，从不灰心放弃。
EN: He is not afraid of difficulties, and never loses heart to give up.

ZH: 灰心放弃只会让你后悔不已。
EN: Losing heart and giving up will only lead to regrets.

ZH: 失败不是理由，我们不能灰心。
EN: Failure is not a reason for us to lose heart.

ZH: 不管前方多么曲折，我们都不能灰心。
EN: No matter how winding the road ahead is, we must not lose heart.
